fields.description:
When using s3cmd with sigv4 enabled the s3 put <filename> s3://<bucket name> will attempt to upload the file as a multi-part file. This will cause the errors below seen in the debug output:
{code}
[shl1@euca-128-84-11-135 Downloads]$ s3cmd -c ~/.s3cfg.euca4-ceph --debug put test90M.file s3://shl1-test
DEBUG: s3cmd version 1.6.1
DEBUG: ConfigParser: Reading file '/home/shl1/.s3cfg.euca4-ceph'
DEBUG: ConfigParser: access_key->AK...17_chars...W
DEBUG: ConfigParser: bucket_location->US
DEBUG: ConfigParser: cloudfront_host->cloudfront.amazonaws.com

DEBUG: ConfigParser: gpg_decrypt->%(gpg_command)s -d --verbose --no-use-agent --batch --yes --passphrase-fd %(passphrase_fd)s -o %(output_file)s %(input_file)s
DEBUG: ConfigParser: gpg_encrypt->%(gpg_command)s -c --verbose --no-use-agent --batch --yes --passphrase-fd %(passphrase_fd)s -o %(output_file)s %(input_file)s
DEBUG: ConfigParser: gpg_passphrase->...-3_chars...
DEBUG: ConfigParser: guess_mime_type->True
DEBUG: ConfigParser: host_base->objectstorage.euca4-ceph.cac.cornell.edu:8773
DEBUG: ConfigParser: host_bucket->objectstorage.euca4-ceph.cac.cornell.edu:8773
{code}
This failure is not seen when uploding the file directly to Ceph. It appears the problem is in the ObjectStorageAuthenticationHandler.handleUpstream method where chunks are not being authenticated successfully.
fields.summary: s3 multi-part upload fails when using signature v4

comments.body:
Workarounds:
1) Using --disable-multipart will allow the file to upload successfully.
2) increasing multipart_chunk_size_mb  to a value larger than the file being uploaded in the .s3cfg file

Looks like this is due to incorrect http parameter encoding. Relevant signature 4 doc:

{quote}
URI-encode each parameter name and value according to the following rules:

    Do not URI-encode any of the unreserved characters that RFC 3986 defines: A-Z, a-z, 0-9, hyphen ( - ), underscore ( _ ), period ( . ), and tilde ( ~ ).

    Percent-encode all other characters with %XY, where X and Y are hexadecimal characters (0-9 and uppercase A-F). For example, the space character must be encoded as %20 (not using '+', as some encoding schemes do) and extended UTF-8 characters must be in the form %XY%ZA%BC.
{quote}

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/sigv4-create-canonical-request.html

Here is an example commit that updates the s3 signature v4 parameter encoding to use the one from our other signature v4 implementation (with a unit test):

https://github.com/sjones4/eucalyptus/commit/d84bb4649a6e87838d66
[~sjones] Feel free to take this issue if you want.

[~sjones] I have run manual tests, unit tests and regression tests on your fix and all have passed. Do you want me to commit this fix?
http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint_4.4/647/
[~mmunn1], if it looks good to you then please commit the fix.
